<b>Yahni</b> or <b>yakhni</b> is a class of foods found from Greece to India.<p>

In <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../585/2120585.xml">
Persian cuisine</link>, it is a kind of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../298/19651298.xml">
soup</link> or <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../783/19372783.xml">
stock</link>, often served over <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../997/581997.xml">
pilaf</link>.</p>
<p>

In <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../486/12486.xml">
Greek</link> (γιαχνί) and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../427/31427.xml">
Turkish</link> (yahni) cuisine, it is a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../184/73184.xml">
stew</link> of meat, fish, or vegetables in a browned-<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../258/51258.xml">
onion</link> base with <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../234/9940234.xml">
tomato</link>es and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../478/22478.xml">
olive oil</link>.</p>



